<h1>From John Hall</h1>

<div class="docbody">
<div class="opener">
<table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationLeft">Dear Sir</td>
		<td class="salutationRight">Lake Geo. [N.Y.] 8th [<span class="choice addition" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover_choice ] header=[]  body=[ Added &lt;span style='font-size: 90%'&gt;[[2007-03-05]]&lt;/span&gt; ]">Roman calendar month, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">i.e.</span>,</span> October] 22d 1758</td>
	      </tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p>this is the 4th Lr I have wrote you this Campn for all wch have not been so happy as to receve one in return.<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-06-02-0074-fn-0001" id="GEWN-02-06-02-0074-fn-0001-ptr">1</a></p>
<p>I cant account for the Loss of yr <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">illegible</span> any other Way than by attributg it to Business, wch your Warfare must naturally involve you in.<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-06-02-0074-fn-0002" id="GEWN-02-06-02-0074-fn-0002-ptr">2</a> an active mind like yours steadily bent on a glorious persuit, ought not to be weand to a more trifling Attention, that as to this point I freely absolve you, earnestly hoping, when you have divested yourself of Business, youl once more look on me in the Numr of yr Acquaintance.</p>
<p>What may be the fate of our Arms yr Way I know not, but I hope for Success, not more through a Spirit of Patriotism, or the principles of a Soldier than a Certainty of its throwing an additional Lustre, on the Man I esteem.</p>
<p>I read with infinite regret, the Loss off poor Baker &amp; Campbell, I think the Bullets fly your Way as oursThey seem more to be directed by Envy, than guided by fate.<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-06-02-0074-fn-0003" id="GEWN-02-06-02-0074-fn-0003-ptr">3</a></p>
<p>Its out of my power to write any News&amp; Its none to tell you I am with sincere Affection Yr most obt hbe Servt</p>
<div class="closer">
<p class="signed">Jno. Hall</p>
</div>
<div class="postscript">
<p>P.S. My kind Coms. Wait on Majr Halkett &amp; Col. Bird to whom I now writ<span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">mutilated</span>pardn the freedom of the inclos<span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">mutilated</span>.<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-06-02-0074-fn-0004" id="GEWN-02-06-02-0074-fn-0004-ptr">4</a></p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="docback">
<div class="note-source" id="GEWN-02-06-02-0074-sn">

   <p>
<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Autograph Letter Signed: a letter in the handwriting of, and signed by, the author ]">ALS</abbr>, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>.
</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-06-02-0074-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-02-06-02-0074-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>No letter from Hall to GW has been found that is dated after <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-05-02-0066" class="document">Halls letter of 14 Feb. 1758</a> in which Hall acknowledged receipt of a letter sent by GW
<span class="pb" title="page number in print edition (no page scan available)" id="GEWN-02-06-02-pb-0087">[87]</span>
from Mount Vernon. In <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Stanislaus Murray Hamilton, ed. &lt;i&gt;Letters to Washington and Accompanying Papers&lt;/i&gt;. 5 vols. Boston and New York, 18981902. ]">Hamilton, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Letters to Washington</span></span> (3:13940), this letter of 22 Oct. is misdated 22 Dec. 1758. Hall was a lieutenant in GWs regiment until May 1757 when he went to New York and bought an ensigns commission in the 44th Regiment of Foot. At this time he was a lieutenant in the 18th Regiment of Foot.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-06-02-0074-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-02-06-02-0074-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>Hamilton makes out the illegible word to be favr (ibid.).</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-06-02-0074-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-02-06-02-0074-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>Lieutenants James Baker and John Campbell of the 1st Virginia Regiment were among those killed on 14 Sept. near Fort Duquesne.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-06-02-0074-fn-0004-ptr" id="GEWN-02-06-02-0074-fn-0004">4</a>

   <p>The enclosures to Francis Halkett and William Byrd have not been found.</p>

</div>
</div>
